verbose_text: The results of our subsequent in vivo HRMAS 1 H-NMR and EPR experiments support the hypothesis that trauma can reduce insulin signaling through a mechanism that involves a phylogenetically conserved pathway for the regulation of glucose and lipid metabolism, and that SS-31 can promote the recovery of mitochondrial function and alleviate this condition.
evidence: HRMAS  1 H-NMR and EPR experiments support the hypothesis that trauma can reduce insulin
